    q: "Does a sauna heater need a 240V circuit?",
    a: "Almost always, yes. Residential electric sauna heaters above about 3 kW need a dedicated 240V circuit sized to the heater - for example a 6 kW heater on a 30A breaker with #10 wire, or an 8-9 kW heater on a 40A breaker with #8 wire - protected by a GFCI breaker and installed by a licensed electrician. Only small plug-in infrared panels run on a normal 120V outlet; traditional rock heaters do not.",
